{"Main text":"These movies and TV shows are coming to Netflix in May\nAnd here's what's disappearing\nShare on Facebook Tweet Share Pin Share\nApril is nearly over, which means Netflix is doing some spring cleaning on its streaming video selection.\nComing to service next month are movies like Inglorious Basterds (on May 22nd), Fruitvale Station (May 12th), and The Boxtrolls (May 23rd). Netflix will also debut two of its new original series, Grace and Frankie (May 8th) and Between (May 21st), along with the Jen Kirkman comedy special I'm Gonna Die Alone (And I Feel Fine) on May 22nd.\nIt's your last chance to watch Skyfall\nCome May 15th, Netflix is getting two exclusives: the first three seasons of Granite Flats, and street fighting documentary Dawg Fight. Then, on the 29th, it's getting the Rashida Jones-produced documentary Hot Girls Wanted, which explores the amateur porn industry.\nLeaving the service in May are a handful of films, including Skyfall (May 5th), the 1987 version of Robocop (May 1st), and Acadamy Award winner Life Is Beautiful (also on May 1st). Some older films like Airplane!, Along Came Polly, and Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles II: The Secret of the Ooze will all disappear on May 1st.\nVox Video: Netflix's Daredevil has received universal praise\nYes, I would like to receive a daily newsletter from The Verge and occasional dedicated newsletters from sponsors and\/or partners.\nForgot password?\nWe'll email you a reset link.\nIf you signed up using a 3rd party account like Facebook or Twitter, please login with it instead.\nForgot username?\nWe'll email it to you.\nIf you signed up using a 3rd party account like Facebook or Twitter, please login with it instead.\nForgot password?\nIf you signed up using a 3rd party account like Facebook or Twitter, please login with it instead.\nTry another email?\nForgot username?\nIf you signed up using a 3rd party account like Facebook or Twitter, please login with it instead.\nTry another email?\nAlmost done,\n